criteria.driver_alignment:
Represent — student laid out scenarios, metrics (EPS, net cash, stakeholder outcomes, ROIC vs WACC), and assumptions/data needs;  
Implement — student linked the plan to implemented artifacts (Python/Colab model and outputs);  
Validate — sensitivity analysis and sanity checks tied back to the planned metrics.

Discover — framed the problem and stakeholders, highlighting trade-offs and agency conflicts;  
Implement — built and used a quantitative model to calculate EPS, net cash, and run sensitivity tests;  
Reflect — drew the key insight (EPS accretion ≠ value creation) and gave a balanced recommendation acknowledging uncertainty.
